1
00:00:09,708 --> 00:00:11,625
[gunshot]

2
00:00:19,041 --> 00:00:20,750
[KENSUKE gasps]

3
00:00:23,250 --> 00:00:28,250
[grunts]

4
00:00:42,708 --> 00:00:44,250
[KENSUKE gasps]

5
00:00:44,333 --> 00:00:49,291
[YOSHIO continues gasping]

6
00:00:51,208 --> 00:00:55,708
[ARISU'S MOTHER gasps]

7
00:00:55,791 --> 00:01:00,750
[YOSHIO grunts]

8
00:01:03,416 --> 00:01:05,208
[YOSHIO]
It hurts!

9
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:14,458
♪

10
00:02:40,166 --> 00:02:42,958
Kobayashi!

11
00:02:43,041 --> 00:02:46,416
[KENSUKE gasps]

12
00:02:49,166 --> 00:02:51,083
[KENSUKE gasps]

13
00:02:54,083 --> 00:02:57,000
[NAKAMURA gasps]
Hold it!

14
00:03:02,500 --> 00:03:06,000
[KENSUKE]
Why? Why did you do that?

15
00:03:06,083 --> 00:03:09,666
[INOUE] He's bleeding
too much. If this keeps up.

16
00:03:09,750 --> 00:03:11,708
Guess his wish came true.

17
00:03:11,791 --> 00:03:14,541
Your little race
has come to an end.

18
00:03:17,250 --> 00:03:18,166
[grunts]

19
00:03:18,250 --> 00:03:19,291
[KENSUKE]
No matter what it takes,

20
00:03:19,375 --> 00:03:21,541
one day, I'll kill you.

21
00:03:25,291 --> 00:03:29,541
[grunts]
Dammit! I didn't want this!

22
00:03:37,375 --> 00:03:40,000
[AKECHI] See that?
He's losing his juice.

23
00:03:40,083 --> 00:03:42,500
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

24
00:03:42,583 --> 00:03:45,708
This power always kept
him from killing himself.

25
00:03:49,916 --> 00:03:54,291
So, why did it suddenly
decide to let him?

26
00:03:54,375 --> 00:03:56,208
You mean he?

27
00:03:56,291 --> 00:04:00,333
[AKECHI] Yeah. It's the only
thing that makes sense.

28
00:04:00,416 --> 00:04:04,041
[KENSUKE]
What does? I don't get it!

29
00:04:04,125 --> 00:04:06,166
[grunts]

30
00:04:06,250 --> 00:04:10,250
[INOUE] His ability to
prevent death. It's possible,

31
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:14,000
it has a direct correllation
with his desire to die.

32
00:04:14,083 --> 00:04:17,166
If that desire were to fade,
so would his power.

33
00:04:17,250 --> 00:04:18,500
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

34
00:04:18,583 --> 00:04:23,333
[AKECHI] In simple terms.
Kobayashi wants to live.

35
00:04:23,416 --> 00:04:24,666
Poor kid.

36
00:04:24,750 --> 00:04:27,750
[gasps]

37
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:31,875
[KENSUKE] This is messed up.
What's your deal, huh?

38
00:04:31,958 --> 00:04:34,625
You're always telling me
to hurry up and kill you.

39
00:04:36,208 --> 00:04:37,750
[AKECHI]
Who knows?

40
00:04:37,833 --> 00:04:41,083
Maybe he thought you were fun
to be around. Worth living for.

41
00:04:41,166 --> 00:04:42,750
[gasps]

42
00:04:42,833 --> 00:04:46,916
I've got a theory.
Remember the times you got hurt?

43
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,291
[KENSUKE] First at the factory,
then at the venue hall.

44
00:04:49,375 --> 00:04:53,000
Both after you helped someone.
So if we solve a bunch of cases,

45
00:04:53,083 --> 00:04:54,500
you can get hurt
a bunch of times

46
00:04:54,583 --> 00:04:56,750
and finally kick the bucket!

47
00:04:58,041 --> 00:05:03,375
You mean. It was never about
solving cases. It was me?

48
00:05:06,916 --> 00:05:08,666
[KENSUKE grunts]

49
00:05:15,666 --> 00:05:18,583
No. No. It's not fair!

50
00:05:18,666 --> 00:05:20,208
[AKECHI sighs]

51
00:05:24,291 --> 00:05:29,000
[AKECHI grunts] If we can't
touch him, we can't treat him,

52
00:05:29,083 --> 00:05:31,250
let alone carry him out of here.

53
00:05:31,333 --> 00:05:33,333
[KENSUKE]
Then what do we do?

54
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:37,291
[AKECHI] As much as I
loathe to suggest it.

55
00:05:37,375 --> 00:05:40,083
The only way to save him now
is to make him want to die.

56
00:05:40,166 --> 00:05:41,458
[KENSUKE gasps]

57
00:05:41,541 --> 00:05:45,750
If we can do that,
his power'll save his life.

58
00:05:45,833 --> 00:05:48,708
Though that might be crueler
than just letting him go.

59
00:05:48,791 --> 00:05:52,458
[KENSUKE] How're we
supposed to choose for him?

60
00:05:52,541 --> 00:05:54,083
You're the one who
made Koba wanna live

61
00:05:54,166 --> 00:05:57,291
in the first place.
It's your call.

62
00:05:57,375 --> 00:05:59,708
[KENSUKE grunts]

63
00:05:59,791 --> 00:06:02,833
Whatever you decide,
I won't be any part of it.

64
00:06:05,541 --> 00:06:07,208
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

65
00:06:08,583 --> 00:06:11,000
[AKECHI]
Don't follow me around anymore.

66
00:06:11,083 --> 00:06:12,666
[INOUE]
Boss, wait.

67
00:06:12,750 --> 00:06:15,541
[AKECHI] The Boy Detective's
club is disbanded.

68
00:06:16,958 --> 00:06:17,916
[KENSUKE gasps]

69
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,291
[INOUE grunts]

70
00:06:19,375 --> 00:06:22,500
Disbanded? Why?

71
00:06:27,250 --> 00:06:28,833
[NORO gasps]

72
00:06:51,458 --> 00:06:54,333
[ARISU'S MOTHER grunts]

73
00:06:54,416 --> 00:06:57,041
[gun clicks]

74
00:06:57,125 --> 00:06:59,416
[ARISU'S MOTHER grunts]

75
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:00,791
Don't even try it.

76
00:07:00,875 --> 00:07:02,750
[ARISU'S MOTHER gasps]

77
00:07:10,625 --> 00:07:12,083
[NAKAMURA gasps]

78
00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:17,958
[ARISU'S MOTHER gasps]

79
00:07:18,041 --> 00:07:19,625
[HIDE] Where the hell
have you been, lady?

80
00:07:19,708 --> 00:07:23,083
We were looking everywhere.

81
00:07:23,166 --> 00:07:26,916
And, by the way, what was with
all that trigger happy nonsense?

82
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,791
You said you'd only
use it for revenge.

83
00:07:28,875 --> 00:07:32,416
The last time I checked, this
cop didn't murder your daughter.

84
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:36,291
[NAKAMURA] Who are you?
What's your involvement here?

85
00:07:36,375 --> 00:07:39,000
[HIDE] Sorry, miss. Wish I
could stick around and chat,

86
00:07:39,083 --> 00:07:42,208
but she and I have a date
with a getaway car.

87
00:07:45,375 --> 00:07:47,083
[NAKAMURA grunts]

88
00:07:47,916 --> 00:07:49,708
[gasps]

89
00:07:53,875 --> 00:07:58,833
[NAKAMURA grunts]

90
00:08:07,708 --> 00:08:09,583
[NAKAMURA grunts]

91
00:08:18,333 --> 00:08:20,666
[KENSUKE gasps]

92
00:08:22,250 --> 00:08:23,958
[NORO]
Inoue.

93
00:08:24,041 --> 00:08:27,333
Did Akechi tell you he was
going to break up the club?

94
00:08:27,416 --> 00:08:29,625
We'll talk about that later.

95
00:08:29,708 --> 00:08:31,416
[NORO]
You kept me out of the loop?

96
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:34,208
After everything we've
been through together?

97
00:08:34,291 --> 00:08:35,833
I said later, Noro!

98
00:08:35,916 --> 00:08:37,916
[NORO]
No! You owe me that much!

99
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:41,916
If you've got some excuse,
I want to hear it!

100
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:43,791
[gasps]

101
00:08:43,875 --> 00:08:45,416
[NORO]
Inoue!

102
00:08:46,041 --> 00:08:51,041
[INOUE grunts]

103
00:08:51,666 --> 00:08:55,208
[NORO gasps]
What are you doing?

104
00:08:55,291 --> 00:09:00,250
[INOUE grunts]

105
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:04,833
It'll work.

106
00:09:04,916 --> 00:09:06,583
I don't follow.

107
00:09:06,666 --> 00:09:08,416
Grab the curtain!

108
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:10,208
[KENSUKE]
Uh...

109
00:09:18,416 --> 00:09:20,125
[gasps]

110
00:09:21,708 --> 00:09:22,833
[INOUE]
We'll pick him up with this

111
00:09:22,916 --> 00:09:24,708
and put him in my wheelchair.

112
00:09:24,791 --> 00:09:26,166
Understood.

113
00:09:28,916 --> 00:09:31,041
[INOUE]
Be careful.

114
00:09:31,125 --> 00:09:33,666
If we drop him,
we're out of options.

115
00:09:44,083 --> 00:09:45,791
[sighs]

116
00:09:45,875 --> 00:09:47,708
[grunts]

117
00:09:53,083 --> 00:09:58,041
[police sirens blaring]

118
00:10:09,375 --> 00:10:12,458
Put an APB out! They've already
got a head start.

119
00:10:12,541 --> 00:10:13,583
[MIYANISHI]
Hey, boss.

120
00:10:13,666 --> 00:10:15,583
[NAKAMURA grunts]
You're late.

121
00:10:15,666 --> 00:10:18,291
[MIYANISHI grunts]
Gee, thanks for the concern.

122
00:10:18,375 --> 00:10:21,250
It's not like I broke out of
the hospital or anything.

123
00:10:21,333 --> 00:10:23,250
You could at least try
to praise me a little bit.

124
00:10:23,333 --> 00:10:27,208
[NAKAMURA grunts]
The case is over. Or is it?

125
00:10:27,291 --> 00:10:28,833
[MIYANISHI]
Huh?

126
00:10:28,916 --> 00:10:30,333
[BOSS D]
Nakamura!

127
00:10:30,416 --> 00:10:31,291
[NAKAMURA, MIYANASHI gasp]

128
00:10:31,375 --> 00:10:33,125
[BOSS D growls]

129
00:10:33,208 --> 00:10:34,541
Shoot me.

130
00:10:34,625 --> 00:10:37,000
[BOSS D] I knew you'd find
a way to screw this up.

131
00:10:37,083 --> 00:10:39,666
I have half a mind to make you
a meter maid for the rest

132
00:10:39,750 --> 00:10:40,875
of your career, but you'd
probably screw that up, too!

133
00:10:40,958 --> 00:10:42,333
[NAKAMURA]
Miyanishi, come here.

134
00:10:42,416 --> 00:10:43,500
[MIYANISHI]
Hm?

135
00:10:43,583 --> 00:10:45,375
[BOSS D] 
...stop making trouble for--

136
00:10:45,458 --> 00:10:48,583
[BOSS D growls]
Nakamura! Over here. Now!

137
00:10:48,666 --> 00:10:49,958
[NAKAMURA grunts]

138
00:10:52,041 --> 00:10:53,416
[MIYANISHI]
hm?

139
00:11:00,500 --> 00:11:02,708
[NORO] Should I send the
car to the back entrance?

140
00:11:02,791 --> 00:11:04,041
Sure.

141
00:11:04,125 --> 00:11:05,250
[NORO]
I'm on it.

142
00:11:06,458 --> 00:11:07,625
Go.

143
00:11:07,708 --> 00:11:09,166
[KENSUKE gasps]

144
00:11:09,250 --> 00:11:12,125
When the car gets here, take
Kobayashi back to the office.

145
00:11:12,208 --> 00:11:13,875
[KENSUKE grunts]

146
00:11:13,958 --> 00:11:16,416
You don't want the police
finding him, right?

147
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:18,125
Good point.

148
00:11:18,208 --> 00:11:19,666
Then...

149
00:11:21,875 --> 00:11:23,500
[KENSUKE grunts]

150
00:11:24,666 --> 00:11:27,791
Don't worry about me.
Just get going.

151
00:11:27,875 --> 00:11:31,000
Huh?! No freakin' way. Come on!

152
00:11:31,083 --> 00:11:32,500
[KENSUKE gasps]

153
00:11:32,583 --> 00:11:34,208
Go!

154
00:11:36,375 --> 00:11:38,250
[KENSUKE exhales]

155
00:11:43,541 --> 00:11:45,000
[INOUE, KENSUKE gasp]

156
00:11:46,291 --> 00:11:53,208
Uh. Hey. This a bad time?
I can always come back later.

157
00:12:25,333 --> 00:12:29,000
[grunts]

158
00:12:32,875 --> 00:12:35,666
[INOUE] Sorry. You shouldn't
be doing this when you're hurt.

159
00:12:35,750 --> 00:12:40,875
[MIYANISHI] This?
Just a scratch. No biggie.

160
00:12:40,958 --> 00:12:45,625
Besides, this is hardly the
time to be worrying about me.

161
00:12:45,708 --> 00:12:50,416
Still, we appreciate the help.
But, why are you here?

162
00:12:50,500 --> 00:12:54,375
[MIYANISHI] Huh? Oh, Nakamura
sent me to check on you guys.

163
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:57,666
Nakamura did?

164
00:12:57,750 --> 00:13:02,458
Yeah. She's a little bit
occupied at the moment.

165
00:13:02,541 --> 00:13:05,666
[BOSS D] You know what
you are? An embarrassment!

166
00:13:05,750 --> 00:13:08,208
This is exactly why I was
against this operation

167
00:13:08,291 --> 00:13:11,916
from the beginning!
That damn detective agency,

168
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:14,583
or club, whatever the
hell they are.

169
00:13:14,666 --> 00:13:17,583
Yet you hired them and
what happened? Disaster!

170
00:13:17,666 --> 00:13:20,375
[NAKAMURA]
I know. This is all my fault.

171
00:13:20,458 --> 00:13:22,375
I'll take full responsibility.

172
00:13:22,458 --> 00:13:24,500
[BOSS D]
Damn right you will.

173
00:13:24,583 --> 00:13:26,958
Finally, something we
can agree on.

174
00:13:27,041 --> 00:13:30,125
However, don't you dare
think you're the only one

175
00:13:30,208 --> 00:13:33,125
who has to shoulder
this disgrace. We all do!

176
00:13:33,208 --> 00:13:36,000
The entire police force.
Hope you're happy!

177
00:13:36,083 --> 00:13:37,875
[grunts]

178
00:13:37,958 --> 00:13:39,750
[MIYANISHI]
Going to the office?

179
00:13:39,833 --> 00:13:42,125
Move over, I can
drive you there.

180
00:13:42,208 --> 00:13:43,708
No, you've already done plenty.

181
00:13:43,791 --> 00:13:46,583
We couldn't possibly
ask anymore of you.

182
00:13:46,666 --> 00:13:48,541
Besides...

183
00:13:51,666 --> 00:13:53,708
[INOUE]
...this is our problem.

184
00:13:58,958 --> 00:14:03,916
[HIDE hums]

185
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:11,125
[humming continues]

186
00:14:11,208 --> 00:14:12,666
[HIDE chuckles]

187
00:14:22,750 --> 00:14:24,208
[HIDE grunts]

188
00:14:24,291 --> 00:14:27,291
Stop by the hideout first so
we can drop off the old lady.

189
00:14:27,375 --> 00:14:28,541
And then?

190
00:14:28,625 --> 00:14:32,958
You really need to ask?
We make a house call.

191
00:14:35,916 --> 00:14:40,875
[YOSHIO gasps]

192
00:15:01,083 --> 00:15:06,083
[YOSHIO grunts]

193
00:15:11,166 --> 00:15:12,625
Kobayashi!

194
00:15:12,708 --> 00:15:14,583
[YOSHIO grunts]

195
00:15:14,666 --> 00:15:16,583
[KENSUKE]
Take this!

196
00:15:16,666 --> 00:15:20,291
It's medicine! Hold out
your hand. Hurry!

197
00:15:20,375 --> 00:15:24,208
[YOSHIO gasps]

198
00:15:24,291 --> 00:15:27,541
Come on! It'll help you!
I can't give it to you.

199
00:15:29,250 --> 00:15:33,958
[KENSUKE] Do you understand?
You gotta do it yourself.

200
00:15:34,041 --> 00:15:37,250
Take it, Koba. Please?

201
00:15:37,333 --> 00:15:41,083
Please! Kobayashi,
take the freaking pill!

202
00:15:47,458 --> 00:15:50,875
[KENSUKE gasps]

203
00:15:50,958 --> 00:15:52,541
Damn you!

204
00:15:59,625 --> 00:16:02,125
[NORO] Isn't there
anything you can do?

205
00:16:02,208 --> 00:16:04,333
[INOUE]
If there were, I'd do it.

206
00:16:09,791 --> 00:16:14,750
[KENSUKE grunts, growls]

207
00:16:18,666 --> 00:16:21,875
[KENSUKE]
Dammit. Dammit!

208
00:16:21,958 --> 00:16:26,958
[KENSUKE sobs]

209
00:16:27,666 --> 00:16:32,375
The only way to save him now
is to make him want to die.

210
00:16:33,666 --> 00:16:36,666
How the hell am supposed
to do that, Boss?

211
00:16:36,750 --> 00:16:41,458
You made it
sound easy. It's not!

212
00:16:41,541 --> 00:16:44,916
[KENSUKE grunts]

213
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:47,083
[KENSUKE, INOUE gasp]

214
00:16:50,041 --> 00:16:51,708
[gasps]

215
00:16:51,791 --> 00:16:53,791
How's it goin?

216
00:16:53,875 --> 00:16:55,333
[KENSUKE]
Why are you here?

217
00:16:55,416 --> 00:16:59,583
What a silly question.
I came to get you, of course.

218
00:16:59,666 --> 00:17:01,000
Huh?

219
00:17:01,083 --> 00:17:04,166
It's party time!

220
00:17:04,250 --> 00:17:05,708
Not really.

221
00:17:05,791 --> 00:17:08,833
We're going over the failed
mission and licking our wounds.

222
00:17:08,916 --> 00:17:10,875
[NORO]
Huh? What's happening?

223
00:17:10,958 --> 00:17:12,875
You know this person?

224
00:17:12,958 --> 00:17:15,250
Uh... Yeah?

225
00:17:15,333 --> 00:17:17,750
[HIDE laughs]

226
00:17:21,291 --> 00:17:24,916
That's the guy, right?
The invincible badass?

227
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:27,625
Dude... Whoa!

228
00:17:27,708 --> 00:17:30,125
He's bleedin' like crazy!

229
00:17:30,208 --> 00:17:33,000
I'm confused. I thought
he could deflect bullets

230
00:17:33,083 --> 00:17:35,791
with his mind or something.
How'd he get hurt?

231
00:17:35,875 --> 00:17:41,500
Wait. When you said "failed
mission", did you mean Fukiya?

232
00:17:41,583 --> 00:17:45,041
Yup. An eye for an eye.
The whole point of this

233
00:17:45,125 --> 00:17:48,875
operation was to get revenge
for the girl's family.

234
00:17:48,958 --> 00:17:51,416
You organized this catastrophe?

235
00:17:51,500 --> 00:17:54,833
Uh... Organizing ain't my style.

236
00:17:54,916 --> 00:17:57,666
More like, "volunteered
to help out".

237
00:17:57,750 --> 00:18:01,166
This is serious!
Why all the secrecy?

238
00:18:01,250 --> 00:18:03,000
[KENSUKE grunts]

239
00:18:03,083 --> 00:18:04,458
Well, I...

240
00:18:04,541 --> 00:18:07,666
[HIDE] Y'mean, Han didn't
tell you about any of this?

241
00:18:07,750 --> 00:18:08,916
No, he didn't.

242
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:10,541
[KENSUKE gasps]

243
00:18:10,625 --> 00:18:12,791
Why'd you hide this from us?

244
00:18:12,875 --> 00:18:15,625
[KENSUKE]
I wasn't hiding it!

245
00:18:15,708 --> 00:18:16,791
Besides, I ditched them--

246
00:18:16,875 --> 00:18:19,125
[INOUE]
Making excuses?

247
00:18:19,208 --> 00:18:22,916
I don't need them.
Tell it to Kobayashi.

248
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:25,833
[KENSUKE exhales]

249
00:18:25,916 --> 00:18:28,791
[INOUE] He's got one foot
in the grave because of you.

250
00:18:31,625 --> 00:18:33,625
Give the guy a break, man.

251
00:18:33,708 --> 00:18:36,166
He had literally
nothing to do with this.

252
00:18:36,250 --> 00:18:37,916
It was just a
weird twist of fate.

253
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:39,583
No one asked you.

254
00:18:39,666 --> 00:18:41,583
This is our problem.
Stay out of it!

255
00:18:41,666 --> 00:18:46,916
[HIDE grunts] 'Fraid I
can't go along with that.

256
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,375
No matter what happened,

257
00:18:48,458 --> 00:18:51,333
Han is a life-time member of
Hide and the Hooligans.

258
00:18:51,416 --> 00:18:53,541
[KENSUKE, INOUE gasp]

259
00:18:57,458 --> 00:18:59,791
[INOUE]
So that's how it is, huh?

260
00:19:05,250 --> 00:19:07,083
[KENSUKE grunts]

261
00:19:16,291 --> 00:19:18,458
[INOUE]
Must feel good, Kensuke.

262
00:19:18,541 --> 00:19:20,708
You made new friends.
How nice for you.

263
00:19:20,791 --> 00:19:24,291
[KENSUKE gasps] You don't
have to put it like that!

264
00:19:25,666 --> 00:19:31,708
I was hurting. I... just wanted
things to feel normal.

265
00:19:31,791 --> 00:19:36,291
Then... I realized it'd
never be the same again.

266
00:19:36,375 --> 00:19:40,041
I've changed and
I can't undo it.

267
00:19:41,208 --> 00:19:46,833
[KENSUKE sniffs] And I'm not
the only one who changed!

268
00:19:52,291 --> 00:19:57,333
No good stayin' here, Han.
Come with me and we'll Par-tay!

269
00:19:57,416 --> 00:19:59,833
Ugh. I really need to stop that.

270
00:20:12,458 --> 00:20:16,458
[HIDE gasps] Hey, I'm the
leader! I go first!

271
00:20:29,458 --> 00:20:31,166
[INOUE sighs]

272
00:20:36,708 --> 00:20:39,833
[AKECHI] The Boy Detective's
club is disbanded.

273
00:20:42,125 --> 00:20:46,625
Dammit, boss, you didn't
have to come out and say it.

274
00:20:46,708 --> 00:20:50,125
I think we already
knew the truth.

275
00:20:50,208 --> 00:20:51,750
After all...

276
00:20:53,750 --> 00:20:57,416
...you left and you
didn't look back.

277
00:20:57,500 --> 00:20:59,166
[YOSHIO grunts]

278
00:20:59,250 --> 00:21:00,625
[INOUE gasps]

279
00:21:01,833 --> 00:21:06,791
[grunting continues]

280
00:21:10,458 --> 00:21:12,416
[INOUE gasps]

281
00:21:29,625 --> 00:21:34,583
♪

282
00:23:05,208 --> 00:23:09,208
[TWENTY-FACES chuckles]
I wonder.

283
00:23:09,291 --> 00:23:11,791
Do you think your new
toy could give me

284
00:23:11,875 --> 00:23:14,541
the thrills I crave, Akechi?

285
00:23:40,250 --> 00:23:43,041
[TWENTY-FACES]
"Mistaken Absolute Evil."

